## 20. 30-second recap

This reading explains that the SRO and VRO are not competing models, but complementary ones. The **SRO** ensures that projects support long-term strategic priorities, while the **VRO** ensures that these projects deliver measurable business value. Their integration improves resource allocation, decision-making, and continuous improvement, especially in complex organizations. To work well, this integration requires clear roles, regular communication, shared KPIs, and strong feedback loops. The Coca-Cola and P&G case studies show how this dual logic can support both strategic direction and investment performance.

